summary:
30. Welcomes efforts to promote dialogue with opposition elements, calls for implementation of the Action Plan on Peace, Justice and Reconciliation.

31. Welcomes cooperation with the Security Council Committee established pursuant to resolution 1267 (1999).

32. Welcomes regional cooperation initiatives, stresses the importance of increasing cooperation against extremist groups.

33. Calls for strengthened regional economic cooperation, including measures to facilitate trade, increase foreign investments, and develop infrastructure.
34. Recognizes the importance of voluntary, safe, orderly return and sustainable reintegration of Afghan refugees for stability in the country and region, and calls for continued international assistance; 
35. Affirms the importance of voluntary, safe, orderly return and sustainable reintegration of internally displaced persons; 
36. Requests the Secretary-General to report to the Council every three months on developments in Afghanistan, and to develop benchmarks for measuring progress in implementing UNAMA's mandate, and calls for cooperation with UNAMA; 
37. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
